<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,384,879]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="2004" box="[151,426,384,410]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Formicococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lingnani">
<emphasis box="[151,426,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Formicococcus lingnani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, D. J." box="[665,851,384,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" pagination="109 - 188" refId="ref8180" refString="Williams, D. J. (1970) The mealybugs (Homoptera, Coccoidea, Pseudococcidae) of sugar-cane, rice and sorghum. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 60, 109 - 188. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300034209" type="journal article" year="1970">Williams (1970)</bibRefCitation>
from material collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[1200,1305,384,410]" name="Malaysia" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1319,1386,384,410]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,252,420,446]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Thailand</collectingCountry>
; he found these materials to be in agreement with the original material from 
<collectingCountry box="[1073,1141,420,446]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">China</collectingCountry>
, with minor morphological differences, hence in 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, D. J." box="[391,575,456,482]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" refId="ref8227" refString="Williams, D. J. (2004) Mealybugs of southern Asia. The Natural History Museum, London, and Southdene SDN, BHD, Kuala Lumpur, 896 pp." type="book" year="2004">Williams (2004)</bibRefCitation>
he made two illustrations based on specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1167,1234,456,482]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1289,1392,456,482]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. He further suggested inclusion of this species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Williams" authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="2004" box="[657,932,492,518]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Exallomochlus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[657,823,492,518]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Exallomochlus</emphasis>
Williams
</taxonomicName>
because of the presence of a sclerotized area on the dorsum and venter of each anal lobe, but retained it in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takahashi" authorityYear="1928" box="[848,1021,529,554]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Formicococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[848,1021,529,554]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Formicococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the presence of anal lobe bars each connected to an anal lobe bar seta. The species has been collected on 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[1048,1248,564,591]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Cyperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundus">
<emphasis box="[1048,1248,564,591]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Cyperus rotundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[1295,1429,564,590]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cyperaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[200,362,600,626]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Areca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="catechu">
<emphasis box="[200,362,600,626]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Areca catechu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="L." box="[411,531,600,626]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Arecaceae</taxonomicName>
) from 
<collectingRegion box="[611,729,600,626]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Karnataka</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[741,799,600,626]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">India</collectingCountry>
(S. Joshi, unpublished data). 
<bibRefCitation author="Danzig, E. M. &amp; Gavrilov-Zimin, I. A." pageId="3" pageNumber="394" refId="ref6813" refString="Danzig, E. M. &amp; Gavrilov-Zimin, I. A. (2015) Palaearctic mealybugs (Homoptera: Coccinea: Pseudococcidae). Part 2. Subfamily Pseudococcinae. Russian Academy of Sciences, Zoological Institute, St. Petersburg, 619 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / zsr / 2015.24.2.236" type="book" year="2015">Danzig &amp; Gavrilov-Zimin (2015)</bibRefCitation>
transferred the species to 
<taxonomicName authority="Laing" authorityName="Laing" authorityYear="1929" box="[522,700,636,662]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Paraputo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[522,628,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Paraputo</emphasis>
Laing
</taxonomicName>
because it has 6 anal ring setae, which is not justifiable based on the facts provided on the revived combination of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="2004" box="[703,826,672,698]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Formicococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis box="[703,826,672,698]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">F. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the discussion above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,384,879]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">
The only molecular phylogenetic study (
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gullan, P. J. &amp; Hodgson, C. J." box="[653,854,708,735]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" pagination="51 - 71" refId="ref7255" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J. &amp; Hodgson, C. J. (2008) A subfamily-level classification of mealybugs (Hemiptera: Pseudococcidae) based on integrated molecular and morphological data. Systematic Entomology, 33, 51 - 71. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2007.00408. x" type="journal article" year="2008">
Hardy 
<emphasis box="[732,782,708,734]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
) that has included examples of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laing" authorityYear="1929" box="[1209,1315,709,734]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Paraputo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1209,1315,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Paraputo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found that the sampled African species was not related to the sampled Neotropical species. There appear to have been no molecular phylogenetic studies including species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takahashi" authorityYear="1928" box="[637,810,781,806]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Formicococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[637,810,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Formicococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takahashi" authorityYear="1928" box="[1037,1210,781,806]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Formicococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1037,1210,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Formicococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laing" authorityYear="1929" box="[1272,1378,781,806]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Paraputo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1272,1378,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Paraputo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may change in the future if informative new data become available; however, the stability of nomenclature is important to users and changes should be avoided unless there is strong justification.
</paragraph>
